60-Second Meeting Summary

> Encryption protects confidentiality by converting plaintext into ciphertext. Symmetric encryption uses a single shared key and is efficient for protecting large amounts of data, while asymmetric encryption uses public and private keys to solve the key distribution problem. RSA is a widely used asymmetric algorithm that enables secure communication, authentication, and digital signatures. Modern systems combine both approaches—using RSA or ECC for key exchange and AES for efficient data encryption.
